1 - \dfrac{x^2}2 + \mathcal{O}(x^4)
\dfrac{\cos(x) - 1}{x^2} = -\dfrac12 + \mathcal{O}(x^2)
\lim_{x \to 0}\dfrac{\cos(x) - 1}{x^2} =\lim_{x \to 0}\left( -\dfrac12 + \mathcal{O}(x^2) \right) = -\dfrac12 + \lim_{x \to 0} \mathcal{O}(x^2) = -\dfrac12
